abstract: PHILADELPHIA, Oct. 30 -- The local market opened with a decline in Lehigh Valley from 34 1/2 to 33 7/8, but the selling seemed to be short stock. After the pressure was removed the price jumped, without a sale, to 34 3/4, and was steady the balance of the session, closing at 1/8 advance. Lehigh Navigation, in sympathy, sold at 51, and Pennsylvania was fractionally lower.
